{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/adapters/fs.rs:3044-3055` now auto-populates new rows from the live milestone snapshot whenever the caller omits `plan_hash`, and `src/adapters/fs.rs:3343-3355` later treats that stored value as authoritative. That still breaks lineage when the plan changes after dispatch but before `record_task_run_start` runs: a bead dispatched under v1 can be recorded as v2 if `persist_plan` advances the snapshot first, and finalization with the later-discovered true v1 hash then fails with a false `conflicting plan_hash` error. The new comment already describes this race, so the amendment is still incomplete. Add a regression test for `dispatch under v1 -> snapshot advances to v2 -> start without plan_hash -> complete with explicit v1`, and avoid stamping the current snapshot hash onto a new row unless it is known to match the dispatched attempt.","rationale":"This is a correctness issue, not just metadata drift: the row can carry the wrong lineage and the run can become impossible to finalize once the controller supplies the real plan hash."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone lineage/journal changes in `src/adapters/fs.rs` and the related service/model coverage, and ran `cargo test milestone_record::service` plus `cargo test milestone_record::model`. One blocking correctness gap remains in the new-row `plan_hash` auto-population path."}